祸不单行：全球最大实体游戏零售商快因为疫情玩完了。
Misfortunes never come singly: the world's largest physical game retailer is fast running out of steam.
跳跳。
Jump.
文化。
Culture.
1天前。
One day ago.
“2019年是GameStop未来十年中最好的一年。
"2019 is the best year for GameStop in the next decade.
”。
"
在度过一个惨淡的2019年之后，GameStop看来要迎来一个更加惨淡的2020年了。
After a dismal 2019, GameStop looks set for an even bleaker 2020.
。
.
这家全球最大、拥有数千家连锁零售店的实体游戏销售商、二手游戏中介商从2016年开始，就面临着销售额不断下滑的窘境。
The world's largest physical game seller with thousands of retail chains and second-hand game dealers has faced declining sales since 2016.
2018年他们亏损了6亿美元，2019年第一季度的净收入同比下降了75%，沦落到连股息都发不出来。
After losing $600 million in 2018, net income in the first quarter of 2019 fell 75% year-on-year, to the point where they could not pay dividends.
。
.
2019年6月初宣布停发股息后，GameStop的股价立刻暴跌。
Shares in GameStop plunged immediately after the dividend was suspended in early June 2019.
股息停发，GameStop的股价应声下跌了3成。
Shares in GameStop fell 30% after the dividend was suspended.
可就连这种饮鸩止渴的手段也没能止住颓势，去年第二季度，GameStop又净亏损4个多亿美元。
Even this cure hasn't stopped the slide, with GameStop posting a net loss of more than $400 million in the second quarter.
他们唯一停止亏损的尝试似乎就是关店：从2018年末的近7000家关到2019年中的5000多家，在去年第二季度又关了近200家店之后，第三季度又给了GameStop一拳：销售额再度下滑25.7%。
Their only attempt to stop the loss appears to have been to close shops: from nearly 7,000 in late 2018 to more than 5,000 by mid-2019, closing nearly 200 more in the second quarter of last year, before hitting GameStop in the third quarter: sales fell 25.7% again.
。
.
GameStop本来预定在2020年继续推进转型计划，开展更多线下活动（比如电竞比赛和嘉年华），不再单纯卖光碟。
GameStop was scheduled to continue its transformation programme in 2020, with more offline activities (such as Atletico and Fiesta), rather than selling optical discs alone.
然后后来发生的一切我们都知道了。
And then we all know what happened.
。
.
疫情袭来，国内到欧美，所有线下的人群聚集地全部是重点防护区域。
When the epidemic hit, from home to Europe and the United States, all the people under the line gathered in the key protection areas.
。
.
GameStop门店是典型的疫情传播高危区域。
GameTop stores are typically high risk areas for the spread of the epidemic.
GameStop很快宣布取消包括Doom和《动物森友会》午夜发布在内的所有午夜发布活动，但是白天暂不关闭门店，而是“向所有门店发放卫生用品，保证100%的清洁措施”，他们还规定门店内同时只能有10位顾客，需要接触的主机设备全部暂时停用。
GameStop quickly announced the cancellation of all midnight launches, including Doom and the Animal Friends, but instead of closing stores during the day, they "distributed hygiene items to all stores to ensure 100% cleanliness." They also limited stores to 10 customers at a time, suspending all mainframe equipment they needed to reach.
。
.
但是据门店的员工反映，在很多地方，GameStop没能执行他们承诺的这些措施。
But in many places, GameStop has failed to implement the measures it promised, according to store staff.
恐慌的员工们给Kotaku和Polygon等外媒写了匿名信，称即使在一些疫情严重、强制关闭非必要商店的地区，GameStop也没有关闭门店。
Panicked employees wrote anonymous letters to agents such as Kotaku and Polygon, saying GameStop had not shut down stores even in areas with severe epidemics and forced closures of non-essential stores.
。
.
一位门店经理在信中说，公司的电话会议要求各门店保持营业，不要管各州的要求，如果有员工被确诊了新冠，那么所有人将被隔离——但是在该门店清洁后，公司会派新一批员工继续营业。
A store manager wrote that the company's conference calls require stores to remain open, regardless of state requirements, and that if anyone is diagnosed with a new crown, everyone will be quarantined - but after the store is cleaned, a new group of employees will be sent to continue operations.
而生病或者生病者有接触的员工在家隔离期间，仍然需要使用个人病假或事假，公司尚未制定任何紧急病假工资政策。
The use of personal sick leave or family leave is still required during home isolation for employees who are sick or in contact with sick people, and the company has not established any emergency sick pay policy.
。
.
GameStop承诺的清洁措施也不怎么靠谱。
Nor are the cleaning measures promised by GameStop credible.
在书面文件中，公司要求门店员工30分钟洗一次手，定期清洁地面，但是文件同时指出：“数周内公司无法提供所需的清洁用品”，需要当地管理人员先去购买，然后向公司报销。
In the paperwork, store staff were asked to wash their hands once a day and clean the floor regularly, but the document also noted that "cleaning products are not available for weeks" and needed to be purchased by local managers and reimbursed by the company.
。
.
“当地的管理人员”当然也买不到清洁用品。
"Local managers" cannot, of course, buy cleaning materials.
疫情越严重的地区，洗手液、消毒液等清洁用品越快被抢购一空，而正是这些地区的门店更需要清洁卫生。
The more severe the outbreak, the quicker cleaning products, such as hand sanitizers and disinfectants, are snapped up, and it is in these areas that stores need to be cleaner.
据匿名信中说，已经有门店全员共用两瓶洗手液，还有一瓶是从隔壁的店里借来的。
According to the anonymous letter, two bottles of hand sanitizer have been shared by all staff and one has been borrowed from the store next door.
门店运营中需要员工频繁接触货柜、实体游戏包装，但GameStop也没能提供足够的手套。
Shop operations require frequent contact with containers, physical game packaging, but GameStop also failed to provide enough gloves.
。
.
更有甚者，据称，一位地区主管要求一家门店举办“技术贸易活动”，要求员工不要以任何理由拒绝交易，而是“充分利用增长的流量”（指大家在家期间对游戏的需求增长）。
What's more, a district executive allegedly asked a store to organize a "technology trade" and told employees not to refuse to trade for any reason, but to "make the most of the growth in traffic" (the growing demand for games while they were at home).
。
.
GameStop的不作为引起了员工的不满。
GameStop's inaction has caused dissatisfaction among employees.
有些员工选择不去门店了，却随后得到通知，如果没有医生“责令停工”的证明，他们将被视为旷工，可能会被开除。
Some employees choose not to go to the store and are subsequently informed that they will be considered absent from work and may be expelled if there is no doctor's "order to stop work."
。
.
这些听起来有些不可理喻的行为，可能还是源于GameStop对于公司命运的担忧。
Some of this may sound unreasonable, but it may stem from GameStop's concern about the company's fate.
早在2月初，疫情还没有在海外传播开来时，就有报告称，普遍的士气下跌已经在各个门店里传开，公司高层给予门店的销售压力越来越大，有员工称他们被绝望的管理层压榨。
As early as early February, before the outbreak spread overseas, there were reports of widespread demoralization spreading through stores, mounting pressure from top executives to sell stores and claims by employees that they were being squeezed by desperate management.
。
.
Polygon今年2月中旬的报道。
Polygon reported in mid-February.
一位员工这么形容GameStop 的现状：“公司疯狂而不信任（门店）……你可以在他们发送的每封邮件中感受到，这座建筑正在崩溃。
One employee described GameStop as: "The company is crazy and distrustful... you can feel in every e-mail they send that the building is crumbling."
”。
"
